What is HTML?
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is used to structure content on the web.

What are HTML tags?
Tags are keywords enclosed in angle brackets < > used to define elements.

What is the difference between HTML and HTML5?
HTML5 supports multimedia (<audio>, <video>), semantic tags, local storage, and better APIs.

What are semantic HTML elements?
Elements that clearly describe their meaning, e.g. <header>, <footer>, <article>.

What is the use of <!DOCTYPE html>?
It tells the browser to render the page in HTML5 standard mode.

What is the difference between <div> and <span>?
<div> is block-level, <span> is inline.

What are empty (void) elements?
Elements with no closing tag like <br>, <hr>, <img>.

What is the difference between block and inline elements?
Block elements take full width; inline elements take only required width.

What is the purpose of the <meta> tag?
Provides metadata like charset, description, viewport.

What is the use of alt attribute in <img>?
Improves accessibility and SEO when image fails to load.

What is the difference between id and class?
id is unique; class can be reused.

What are HTML entities?
Used to display reserved characters like &lt; for <.

What is the <iframe> tag?
Embeds another webpage inside the current page.

What is the use of the <label> tag?
Improves accessibility for form inputs.

Forms & Media

What are new form input types in HTML5?
email, date, number, range, tel, url.

Difference between <strong> and <b>?
<strong> has semantic importance; <b> is only visual.

What is the difference between <em> and <i>?
<em> emphasizes meaning; <i> is stylistic.

What is the <canvas> element?
Used for drawing graphics via JavaScript.

What is localStorage and sessionStorage?
Stores data in browser; localStorage persists, sessionStorage ends with session.

How do you make a website responsive using HTML?
Using <meta viewport>, semantic structure, and responsive images.